.TH "blk_rq_map_integrity_sg" 9 "blk_rq_map_integrity_sg" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
blk_rq_map_integrity_sg \- Map integrity metadata into a scatterlist
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" blk_rq_map_integrity_sg
.BI "(struct request_queue *q "  ","
.BI "struct bio *bio "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *sglist "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "q" 12
request queue
.IP "bio" 12
bio with integrity metadata attached
.IP "sglist" 12
target scatterlist
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Map the integrity vectors in request into a
scatterlist.  The scatterlist must be big enough to hold all
elements.  I.e. sized using \fBblk_rq_count_integrity_sg\fP.
